                      <div class="liveblog_post-header">
                          <div class="img_bio-liveglog-wrapper">
                            <img class="img_bio-liveblog" src="https://media1.s-nbcnews.com/j/newscms/2015_31/1142576/nbcnewslogo_6aa4661ea8dd8e9fa847367aed686cd5.nbcnews-fp-320-320.jpg" alt="NBC News">
                          </div>
                        <div class="liveblog_byline-meta-wrapper">
                            <span class="byline byline_liveblog">NBC News</span>
                          <time class="liveblog_byline-timestamp timestamp_liveblog js-timeago" itemprop="datePublished" datetime="2019-02-25T04:19:00.000Z" content="2019-02-25T04:19:00.000Z">5 days ago</time>
                        </div>
                      </div>
                          <header class="nbcnews-dc-header cf">
                            <h2 class="nbcnews-dc-heading"><a href="https://www.nbcnews.com/card/best-picture-goes-green-book-n975531">Best picture goes to... &#x27;Green Book&#x27;</a></h2>
                          </header>
                      <div itemprop="articleBody">
                                          <p> "Green Book" — the tale of the real-life relationship between black pianist Don Shirley (Mahershala Ali) and his Italian-American chauffeur Tony "Lip" Vallelonga (Viggo Mortensen) — took home the biggest award of the night. The film was one of the most divisive, hotly debated movies of 2018, as Ethan Sacks <a href="https://www.nbcnews.com/pop-culture/movies/will-green-book-controversies-turn-away-oscar-voters-n960386" target="_blank">explains here. </a> </p>
                                          <p> <strong>See all the winners of the Oscars <a href="https://www.nbcnews.com/pop-culture/awards/who-won-oscars-full-list-nominees-winners-n971796" target="_blank">here</a>.</strong> </p>
                      </div>
