                          <header class="nbcnews-dc-header cf">
                            <h2 class="nbcnews-dc-heading"><a href="https://www.nbcnews.com/card/hot-take-bradley-cooper-gaga-got-far-shallow-they-ve-n975481">Hot take: Bradley Cooper and Gaga got as far from the &#x27;Shallow&#x27; as they&#x27;ve ever been</a></h2>
                          </header>
                      <div itemprop="articleBody">
                                          <p> Here's the thing: Bradley Cooper and Lady Gaga are not Jackson Maine or Ally, but tonight they would've liked us to believe they were. Because while we've endured a "are they or aren't they" for the entirety of fall and winter, their performance of "Shallow" tonight truly strove to recreate the magic of a fictional couple we'd all hate to hang out with in real life. </p>
                                          <p> So yes, they sang, they duetted, and they ended the song by making it seem like they were about to kiss — only to not, and instead sit awkwardly close as if it wasn't rehearsed, planned, or plotted. Which marks the end of an era! It's over! Jackson and Ally have been retired, long live "Shallow," unless you're tired of it! I just hope Bradley gave Sam Elliott back his voice. </p>
                      </div>
